SUMMARY:Practicing Presence: Mindfulness for a Meaningful Life
DESCRIPTION:Practicing Presence is a four-week mindfulness course designed 
 to help you build a meditation practice that genuinely fits into your life
 —and into the world you live in.We'll meet on four consecutive Tuesday e
 venings from 7–9 PM at the Olio Lighthouse\, beginning April 28.This ser
 ies is for people who are curious about mindfulness\, have tried meditatin
 g before but struggled to sustain a practice\, or are looking for a ground
 ed and supportive way to deepen their relationship with themselves\, other
 s\, and the wider world.We’ll meet as a small sangha of no more than 12 
 people\, creating space for real relationships\, personalized guidance\, a
 nd meaningful conversation.Over four weeks\, you will:Learn foundational m
 indfulness meditation practicesBuild a realistic daily meditation habit us
 ing behavioral science toolsExplore how mindfulness relates to emotions\, 
 relationships\, and the wider worldReceive personalized guidance in a smal
 l group (max 12 people)Leave with a sustainable practice and resources for
  continuing at homeMany people are drawn to meditation because they want m
 ore calm\, clarity\, and presence. They read about mindfulness\, download 
 apps\, attend occasional classes—and still find it difficult to practice
  consistently.This course addresses that gap directly. By integrating cont
 emplative practice with insights from behavioral science\, we focus on bui
 lding a steady\, realistic mindfulness practice that can be sustained in e
 veryday life.Rather than emphasizing extraordinary states in retreat setti
 ngs\, the series centers on what matters most: developing presence in the 
 places it counts—your work\, relationships\, body\, emotions\, and daily
  routines.What You'll ReceiveThis course combines contemplative tradition 
 with practical tools for real life.Guided meditation and teachings: Weekly
  instruction grounded in established mindfulness traditions.Behavioral sci
 ence tools for habit building: Practical strategies to help meditation bec
 ome a consistent part of your daily life.Engaged mindfulness: Exploring ho
 w contemplative practice supports compassionate action without burnout or 
 bypassing.One-on-one mentorship: Each participant receives a private 15-mi
 nute consultation to discuss their practice\, goals\, and challenges.Perso
 nalized practice plan: You'll develop a realistic approach to building min
 dfulness into your schedule and routines.Practice resources: Reflection pr
 ompts and audio recordings of guided meditations for home practice.Weekly 
 micro-challenges: Small experiments for integrating mindfulness into daily
  life—your commute\, meetings\, relationships\, and conversations.The go
 al is simple: not just to learn about mindfulness\, but to leave with a pr
 actice that is already part of your life.Weekly ArcWeek 1: Introduction to
  Mindfulness — body\, breath\, and foundationsWeek 2: Mindfulness of Emo
 tions — meeting experience with compassionWeek 3: The Wise Heart — cul
 tivating kindness\, balance\, and resilienceWeek 4: Bringing Practice into
  the World — relationships\, work\, and daily lifeEach session includes 
 guided meditation\, short teachings\, group reflection\, and practical sup
 port for building a home practice.About the TeacherThis course is taught b
 y Britt Titus\, who is in her second year of a meditation teacher training
  program under Jack Kornfield and Tara Brach.Britt has practiced meditatio
 n since childhood—including a formative period living at an ashram in In
 dia at age nine.Her work brings together three perspectives: contemplative
  practice\, behavioral science\, and humanitarian work in crisis-affected 
 regions around the world. Her teaching focuses on helping people develop m
 editation practices that are both deeply rooted and practically sustainabl
 e in the midst of everyday life.Who This Is ForThis course is open to begi
 nners and experienced meditators alike\, especially those who want:A groun
 ded introduction to mindfulnessSupport building a consistent meditation pr
 acticeA small in-person learning communityPractical tools for integrating 
 mindfulness into daily lifeNo prior meditation experience or spiritual bac
 kground is required.&nbsp\;*No worries if you have to miss a week\, we wil
 l make sure you are caught up with any materials provided during class.Sch
 olarshipsWe have a small number of scholarship spots available for those f
 acing financial barriers. If cost is preventing you from participating\, p
 lease email brittknee007@gmail.com with a short note about why this course
  would be meaningful for you. Scholarships are offered on a first-come fir
 st-serve\, rolling basis.\n\nTickets & info: https://www.viewcy.com/event/
 practicing_presence
URL:https://www.viewcy.com/event/practicing_presence
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1f8d99ac-afeb-4d17-b478-172599c66eb8@viewcy.olio
DTSTAMP:20260422T141218Z
DTSTART:20260501T230000Z
DTEND:20260502T030000Z
SUMMARY:Archives and Time Capsules: What are we Taking\, What are we Leavin
 g Behind? 
DESCRIPTION:Olito is back\, and this time we're focusing on the theme of Ar
 chives. Cultural\, personal\, historical — what do we keep\, and why? Wh
 at gets lost\, and what does that cost us? What's in the box under your be
 d\, the folder on your phone\, the story your grandmother told only once? 
 Who decides what's worth preserving — and whose histories get written ou
 t of the record? And if our ancestors couldn't leave a trace\, what do we 
 owe the future?The topic is inspired by our friends and collaborators behi
 nd TheNewCari.com — a collective of Caribbean creators\, artists\, and e
 ntrepreneurs preserving and uplifting culture through their beloved zine. 
 With their 10th issue\, their publication is a living archive of contempor
 ary Caribbean artistry. We're celebrating its release together with this O
 lito and can’t wait to see all the stories that each of you brings to th
 e mix.&nbsp\;The New Cari's latest issue will be available to flip through
  and purchase on site to take home. Together we’ll connect\, reflect\, a
 nd make some new memories worth archiving.What to expect:&nbsp\;7:00–7:3
 0pm: Arrive\, get settled\, grab a first drink&nbsp\;7:30pm Olito begins 
 — facilitated prompts\, new faces\, good conversation (it's gonna be lik
 e a grown and sexy version of musical chairs)8:30–9:00pm: Free flowing m
 ingling and discussion&nbsp\;9:00pm: DJ set by AKC (Andrea K. Castillo) 
 🔥 We are dancing!&nbsp\;Our venue is in Prospect Heights between Bergen
  and Carlton — exact address and buzzer sent upon RSVP. Come solo or bri
 ng a friend. The vibes are communal and the conversation brings us all tog
 ether.&nbsp\;\n\nTickets & info: https://www.viewcy.com/event/archives_and
 _time_cap
URL:https://www.viewcy.com/event/archives_and_time_cap
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bbd41527-08b8-43cc-8e7a-0d17bc86003c@viewcy.olio
DTSTAMP:20260422T141218Z
DTSTART:20260503T170000Z
DTEND:20260503T193000Z
SUMMARY:Cosmologies of the Breath
DESCRIPTION:Breathwork is a modern term for a practice and a principle that
  every culture around the world has always held sacred: there are ways to 
 breathe that connect us to something beyond ourselves. The hardwiring of o
 ur bodies and our brains is built on the process of breathing\, and this p
 henomenon connects us on a biological\, chemical\, and anatomical level to
  everyone and everything else on this planet that breathes. Rarely\, howev
 er\, do many of us take any time to unpack and unravel the profound implic
 ations of this very simple fact\, or consider how our relationship to brea
 thing can influence the ways we understand ourselves and our place in the 
 broader web of life.&nbsp\;In this Sunday afternoon Olio\, we'll be explor
 ing three basic tenets of breathwork: observation\, agency\, and cosmology
 . Each of these three things influence how we breathe\, and the way that w
 e breathe also influences each of these three things in turn. By taking so
 me luxurious time to explore them\, using our own breathing patterns as th
 e guide\, we will gain for ourselves an authentic relationship with underu
 tilized power and potential of connecting with our own breathing.Throughou
 t the course of this Olio\, we will learn about the ways that breathing in
 teracts with our capacity for perception (observation)\, our ability to ac
 t and respond to our experiences (agency)\, and how it can influence and e
 xpand our worldview (cosmology). This is not a group breathwork session --
  rather it will consist of three rounds of learning\, discussion\, and exp
 eriential mini-journeys that help us land in what we are unpacking in real
 -time\, based on what is emerging from our bodies. All experiences of brea
 thing are welcome - come if you're curious about what the heck breathing e
 ven is\, or if you are a "pulmonaut" hungry for a focused exploration of t
 he depth and range of our breathing experiences.&nbsp\;All are welcome\, e
 ven those who have never thought once about their own breathing! Come wear
 ing comfy clothes and bring a water bottle and your own yoga mat or blanke
 t if you have one. Note packets will be provided.&nbsp\;About the facilita
 torEm Chiappinelli (she/they) is a breathwork facilitator and event organi
 zer who lives in a rural farming community in northern Virginia. She has b
 een in long-term training (1\,000+ hrs) for integrative breathwork across 
 multiple training schools and programs\, and believes that breathing needs
  to be the first go-to tool in anyone’s inner work\, interpersonal\, or 
 survival strategies (including her own!). Em facilitates breathwork sessio
 ns for individuals virtually and in-person\, and you can read more about t
 he sessions here or reach out directly at hello@everydayalive.com.What Is 
 an Olio?Think Olio is an ongoing experiment in lifelong learning.We are a 
 community of open-minded people who gather to exchange ideas with new frie
 nds and connect over art\, literature\, and philosophy.An Olio is what we 
 call the social learning events we’ve been organizing since 2015. Olios 
 are led by a teacher who loves sharing their passions and the room is fill
 ed with curious\, open-minded New Yorkers.&nbsp\;Our goal is to spark new 
 perspectives\, ignite curiosity\, and enjoy ourselves socially—an altern
 ative to typical nightlife options.Disclaimer: By purchasing a ticket\, yo
 u agree to have your photo/video used for social media/marketing materials
 . If you prefer to not have your photo taken\, feel free to send us a note
 . Photo by the unparalleled Erin Pearlman.\n\nTickets & info: https://www.
 viewcy.com/event/whats_stored_in_the
URL:https://www.viewcy.com/event/whats_stored_in_the
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:a076014c-95a9-439d-a993-2f9fd3acf9a9@viewcy.olio
