SUMMARY:Embracing Rock Bottom: A Poetry (Un)happy Hour with Jason Koo
DESCRIPTION:About the Event:One of the main motivations behind a happy hour
  is to drink and be merry\, to shake loose from the unhappiness otherwise 
 prevailing in our lives\, just as one of the main reasons we turn to poetr
 y is to console ourselves in our unhappiness. But we might\, ironically\, 
 end up feeling that unhappiness more intensely by drinking\, just as we mi
 ght call up our darkest feelings by reading poetry—so put the two togeth
 er and we've got ourselves a potent cocktail.In this Poetry (Un)happy Hour
 \, we'll read and discuss poems from Denis Johnson's landmark 1982 collect
 ion The Incognito Lounge—one of the great literary depictions of rock bo
 ttom—and explore the theme of desolation in our own writing. We'll pair 
 this activity with the Corpse Reviver #2\, seeking to rouse ourselves from
  the dead with this pre-Prohibition\, absinthe-laced cocktail intended to 
 cure hangovers—or perhaps\, as The Savoy Cocktail Book's Harry Craddock 
 warned\, to "un-revive the corpse again" if consumed with sufficient enthu
 siasm.Evening Flow5-7pm (optional) - You're invited to attend a reception 
 celebrating the completion of the Olio mural painted by member Meredith St
 ein in our loft space. Come raise a glass and take some time with the art 
 and meeting new friends before the poetry Olio kicks off at 7pm.&nbsp\; 7-
 7:30 PM – Act I: Poetry Happy Hour: Grab a Corpse Reviver #2 (or N/A alt
 ernative)\, settle in\, and ease into the evening with a conversation prom
 pt.7:30-8:15 PM – Act II: Close Reading: A lecture led by Jason Koo\, di
 ving deep into select poems from The Incognito Lounge and the poetics of d
 esolation.8:15-9 PM – Act III: Writing &amp\; Sharing: We disperse to wr
 iting stations throughout the space for generative writing\, then come bac
 k together to share what emerged.10:30 PM – The evening winds down. Ling
 er\, talk\, and enjoy the space as we transition into something more like 
 a house party.Our Teacher for the Evening: Jason KooJason Koo is a second-
 generation Korean American poet born in New York City and raised in Clevel
 and\, Ohio. He is the author of four full-length collections\, most recent
 ly No Rest (Diode Editions\, 2024)\, winner of the Eugene Paul Nassar Poet
 ry Prize and a finalist for AWP's Donald Hall Prize for Poetry. His work h
 as appeared in The American Scholar\, Best American Poetry\, The Missouri 
 Review\, The Village Voice\, and The Yale Review\, and has been recognized
  with fellowships from the National Endowment for the Arts\, the Vermont S
 tudio Center\, and the New York State Writers Institute.He is the founder 
 of Brooklyn Poets and creator of the Bridge\, its innovative mentorship ne
 twork connecting poets worldwide. For that work\, he was named one of Broo
 klyn Magazine's "100 Most Influential People in Brooklyn Culture." He curr
 ently serves as associate teaching professor of English and director of cr
 eative writing at Quinnipiac University.What Is an Olio?Think Olio is an o
 ngoing experiment in lifelong learning. We are a community of open-minded 
 people who gather to exchange ideas with new friends and connect over art\
 , literature\, and philosophy.Check out our full calendarOur $30 membershi
 p gives you two events for the price of one!An Olio is what we call the so
 cial learning events we’ve been organizing since 2015. A blend between a
  lecture and a house party\, Olios are led by a teacher who loves sharing 
 their passions and the room is filled with curious\, open-minded New Yorke
 rs.&nbsp\;Our goal is to spark new perspectives\, ignite curiosity\, and e
 njoy ourselves socially—an alternative to typical nightlife options.Disc
 laimer: By purchasing a ticket\, you agree to have your photo/video used f
 or social media/marketing materials. If you prefer to not have your photo 
 taken\, feel free to send us a note.Photo by Zhi-Da Zhong\n\nTickets & inf
 o: https://www.viewcy.com/event/embracing_rock_bottom
URL:https://www.viewcy.com/event/embracing_rock_bottom
END:VEVENT
