SUMMARY:Dial-up Disco: An Olio House Party
DESCRIPTION:Tickets:This is a member celebration!&nbsp\; To attend this par
 ty you can sign up for our monthly membership which gives you 2 free event
 s each month. &nbsp\;You will then be able to invite one friend to the par
 ty &lt\;3&nbsp\;It's our 11th anniversary and the parents are away\, so we
 're throwing a party.Whether you were at the first living room class with 
 a professor in 2015 or this is your first time hearing about our community
 \, we want to celebrate 11 years of Olio with you.We're playfully leaning 
 back into the joy and wonder of the dial-up era (this is what happens when
  you let 5 millennials plan a party).What to expect:7:30pm: Upon arrival w
 e match you with a group of friends based on our secret witchery\, i.e.\, 
 whoever we think you should meet after a 1-minute conversation8pm: You sit
  with your new friends and discuss a couple of curated prompts related to 
 the dial-up era9-11pm: DJ SASA plays '90s and early 2000s hits and we danc
 e our asses offTake dance breaks to bedazzle\, yo-yo\, and make art (remem
 ber that rainbow scratch-off paper?!)Pop-Tarts\, pizza bites\, and childho
 od cereals fuel our energy throughout the night12-1am: We'll wind down wit
 h tea and stretches and ambient music because we love our bodiesAttire:Dre
 ss how you dressed when you were 11. Or how you wish you dressed!Tickets:T
 his is a member celebration! To attend this party you can sign up for our 
 monthly membership which gives you 2 free events each month. &nbsp\;You wi
 ll then be able to invite one friend to the party &lt\;3&nbsp\;What is Thi
 nk Olio?Think Olio is an ongoing experiment in lifelong learning. We are a
  community of open-minded people who gather to exchange ideas with new fri
 ends and connect over art\, literature\, and philosophy.An Olio is what we
  call the social learning events we’ve been organizing since 2015. A ble
 nd between a lecture and a house party\, Olios are led by a teacher who lo
 ves sharing their passions and the room is filled with curious\, open-mind
 ed New Yorkers.&nbsp\;Six months into creating a venue\, one of our favori
 te feelings has been the moments where we’ve stepped outside of time. We
 ’ve created a space where conversations don’t feel rushed\, people are
  greeted with hugs\, and as a community\, we spontaneously come up with ne
 w ideas (like the dial-up-disco house party) and bring them to life.Our go
 al is to spark new perspectives\, ignite curiosity\, and enjoy ourselves s
 ocially—an alternative to typical nightlife options.Check out our full c
 alendarDisclaimer: By purchasing a ticket\, you agree to have your photo/v
 ideo used for social media/marketing materials. If you prefer to not have 
 your photo taken\, feel free to send us a note.\n\nTickets & info: https:/
